   <abstract displayLabel="Description">Eunice Paddio-Johnson discusses her memories of racism as a child and as an adult, her education and teaching in segregated schools in Saint Helena Parish, efforts to register black voters, her experience as the first black member of the Saint Helena Parish School Board, the roles of the Freemasons and Order of the Eastern Star in the civil rights movement, the Louisiana Education Association, and her work with various civic associations.</abstract>
